{"meta":{"domain":"subjects","kid":"4888","authors":[{"fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre","id":"6"}],"title":"","dates":{"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:14:24 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:14:24 UTC"}},"nodes":[{"index":0,"parent_index":-1,"body":"<p class=\"Paragraph\">The present tense is formed by placing after the verb the particles: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f7c\u0f51\u0f0b\u0f62\u0f7a\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> (assertive), <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f51\u0f74\u0f42\u0f0b <\/span>(testimonial), and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f61\u0f7c\u0f51\u0f0b<\/span> (egophoric). These are formed by adding an existential copula to the suffix<span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"> \u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b<\/span>. The resulting auxiliaries have the same evidential value as the existential copulas. In modern conversational usage, the form <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f72\u0f0b\u0f60\u0f51\u0f74\u0f42\u0f0b<\/span> is often abbreviated to <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">\u0f42\u0f72\u0f66\u0f0b<\/span>.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">In English, these forms may be translated either by the progressive or the simple present depending on the context.<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\">The various forms are presented in the following table:<\/p><p class=\"Paragraph\"><strong>Table: The Present Tense Auxiliaries<\/strong><\/p><table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"> <tbody> <tr> <td width=\"97\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\">Affirmative<\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"152\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\">Interrogative<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\">(without pronoun)<\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"149\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\">Interrogative<\/p> <p class=\"Paragraph\">(with pronouns)<\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"105\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\">Negative<\/p> <\/td> <td width=\"144\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\">Negative Interrogative<\/p> <\/td> <\/tr> <tr>